headline.main: Fillon Clings to French Presidential Race; Party Not Sure
headline.print_headline: Fillon Clings to French Presidential Race; Party Not Sure

lead_paragraph: With the Eiffel Tower as a backdrop, French conservative Francois Fillon clung tenaciously to his presidential candidacy Sunday, emboldened by thousands of supporters at a high-stakes rally aimed at quashing pressure on him to step aside because of impending corruption charges.
